desc:
No permission or No agreement. It always means the act in whatever form or type is unwelcome. There is no consent: 
► When an act or agreement is against a person or persons will; 
► When an act is done by person or persons both known or unknown, by the use of fear, threats, force or other forms of coercion of the victim, guardian or custodian; 
► When an act represents abduction, fraud, manipulation, deception or misrepresentation such as enticement, inducement, misinformation, forgery, tricks, coercion, hostage, allurement, influence, abuse of power and by any means of inducement; 
► When acts lead to death, disability, injury, or physical and mental harm. This includes the use of threats to withhold a benefit to which the person being threatened is entitled to by custom or law; 
► When the person or persons is incapable of giving consent because of his/her youth or because of his/her temporary or permanent mental or physical incapacity. 

 All acts of abuse, violence and harm involve no consent and each one of them is termed a non-consensual act and is criminal whether it happens at home, work or anywhere else:  rape, sexual assault, physical assault, forced marriage, denial of resources and opportunities, psychological/emotional abuse to name a few are all non-consensual acts.
